messages.text: Christian, are you there??
I wish you’d answer.
I really need to know how you could be a part of all of this?
I know your mom was sick…
And I know you and your dad blame her death on the way the world is.
Or was, anyway.
But this…?
Murdering a billion people?
Americans?!
Why?
Because he told me to.
All right?
If he was your father, you’d have done the same.
Thank you for answering.
But no, I wouldn’t have.
That’s right - you’d have just shot him.
I did shoot him. But let’s keep this civil.
I want to thank you for letting my mom go.
She was always good to me.
That day you were at the cabin with my dad...
The day you saw her in the sunlight...
She actually had the cure in the pocket of her lab coat.
I wish you would have known.
You could have saved her -
and been spared the pain of thinking she was gone.
Quite a few people could have spared me that pain.
Including her.
How did she even know about the cabin?
Was there something between her and your dad?
No. She had followed him out there the night before the outbreak.
Or followed me, I should say.
She had suspected for a while that my dad was planning something.
But what she discovered that night was much bigger than what she had originally thought.
Destroying half the planet with this virus?
Yes.
The handful of us who knew about that were there.
Apparently she was outside listening to everything we said.
When she confronted my dad the next morning...
He started all this.
It was the backup plan.
Whose backup plan? Not the army.
No, his. Ours.
It was coming one way or another.
This cleansing.
And once it began...
and your dad was blamed for starting it...
G.I. Joe took charge.
No one questioned him.
You’re saying no one else knew?
There were a handful of like-minded guys we could trust.
Like Private Whitlock? Good call on that one.
Dad fucked up there. He should have called him, not texted.
Trust me, Whitlock was dead either way.
And I was on to you by then.
But why would my mom confront your dad on her own?
She was at the base. She was in charge.
She thought she was safe.
There was nothing he could do to her there.
Except infect her.
Yes.
Why didn’t she inject herself with the cure?
Don’t know.
My best guess is that she only had seconds before she turned.
She chose to try and save everyone else...instead of herself.
So she called in the breach.
How did you know I was immune?
Dad didn’t trust your mom.
He knew she could do what she said she couldn’t.
Especially if she was working with Seth.
You knew him?
No. But dad did.
And he knew they were lying.
And if they were lying...
Mom would certainly have vaccinated me.
But now, our plan has failed.
The world is on the mend.
And I’ve lost another parent.
You’re welcome. And trust me, you’re better off.
I'm fucked, Ada.
Yes, you are.
Now, about this plan...
Did it include kidnapping me?
No. I was supposed to keep you on our side.
You weren’t supposed to wake up until Dallas.
What do you mean, “Wake up?”
The night of the outbreak, when my dad picked you up outside the base...
he gave you a bottle of water.
Yeah. When I jumped into the back of the truck.
It was drugged. You should have slept for a day.
But you didn’t. You woke up while he was cleaning out the cabin.
That threw everything off.
Yeah, well...shit affects me differently, it turns out.
I know. You’re special.
You don’t know the fucking half of it.
What I still don’t get is this:
What happened in San Antonio at Ft. Sam?
I was there. That entire facility is underground.
It’s designed to prevent something like this from getting out.
There’s always a way for shit to go bad, Ada.
But in this instance, it didn’t have to.
The outbreak there didn’t start underground.
That’s why it spread so much faster.
But if only you and GI Joe knew about this fuck-headed “back up plan” of yours...then...who released the virus at Ft. Sam?
Christian?
I did.
Ada?
I’m sorry. So sorry for everything.
Really? Cool.
All is forgiven, then.
Come on home, honey.
You’re being sarcastic.
No shit?!
You fucking tried to kill a billion people, asshole!!
What the hell good does SORRY do anyone?
God damn…
That is far and away the least effective apology to ever make its way through the ether.
I'm surprised your phone didn’t explode.
So I guess saving your mom counts for nothing?
You didn’t save her, dick-tip, you just stopped holding her prisoner.
But, while I wouldn’t expect a Nobel Peace Prize for that sliver of humanity…
Yes, it counts for something. Specifically:
we can lower the estimated body count of your victims to: 999,999,999 dead.
Consider yourself spared.
Oh…and you have my thanks.
You awe-inspiringly insane mother fucker.
You could have just said no.
No.
Now fuck off.
